programmes.show_description: Submerged: A Turkish drought reveals a long-lost Basilica and its secrets, while the hull of a ship in the North Sea answers decades-old questions. (S1, ep 4)
A father and son see mysterious lights near their property and call the sheriff's office. A large craft covers a French town in an odd material. (S2, ep 9)
Local authorities receive over 50 UFO reports in the Chicago area on Halloween night. Multiple sightings of a large flying craft in PA are known as the Buck's County Wave. (S2, ep 10)
Giorgio Tsoukalos takes a look back at the most compelling investigations of all, and events that he believes represent real encounters with extraterrestrial visitors.
Return To Froggy Bayou: Joey and Zak stake out game trails to nab deer-eating gators, while Daniel and Big Tee get creative with their bait. (S11, ep 2)
Skunk Ape Alley: The war against pythons invading the Everglades begins as Troy Landry, his son Chase and snake expert Bill uncover the sepents' breeding grounds. (S2, ep 1)
Oh No He Didn't: Les loses his temper when the kids suggest he sells their failing second store. With the family's livelihood at stake, Seth puts a sneaky plan into action. (S7, ep 12)
Join antiques expert and presenter David Dickinson as more collectors try to sell their items to dealers. Will they strike a deal or take a chance at auction instead? (S9, ep 18)

The Pickers keep an eye on their new warehouse manager as they scour Ontario for bargains. Scott and Sheldon uncover a cache of vintage guitars. (S3, ep 9)
Henry Cole gets excited as he visits automobilia heaven and the three Junketeers come together to flog restored items. (S2, ep 4)
Here Comes the Calvin-ry!: Lisa dons her cowboy gear and brings her money sock along, while Rene sinks his teeth into an unassuming unit and Brandi goes on a scavenger hunt. (S14, ep 11)
Zip Tie Lies: Rene and Casey roll the dice on some sealed totes in San Bernardino, while Kenny stumbles over some odd-looking car parts and Lisa shields herself from disaster. (S14, ep 12)
Pay to Play: Les is caught in a dilemma over the authenticity of a rare guitar. With no expert on hand, he's forced to go with his gut. (S8, ep 2)
Unforgiven: Rich makes a glaring error that could see him fired. Plus, a kooky cowboy arrives at the counter and Ashley reacts to bad manners in the pawn shop queue. (S8, ep 3)
Jurassic Pawn: Chum gets into the teen spirit when a piece of Kurt Cobain memorabilia finds its way into the shop. Rick takes a swing at a National League Championship ring.
The Champ: Troy and Terral protect a friend's fish camp with the help of their ace-in-the-hole sniper. The Edwards go toe-to-toe with a heavyweight gator known as The Champ. (S11, ep 3)
Return to the Everglades Triangle: The hunters venture into the Everglades Triangle, a remote area known for unexplained disappearances and swarms of snakes. (S2, ep 3)

What Lies Below: UAPs have been seen entering the ocean at high speeds - and since our oceans can be as deep as six miles, were the UAPs simply trying to get home? (S1, ep 9)
The Paradox: As the Fermi Paradox states, the likelihood of advanced life in the universe is surprisingly high - so why haven't we had any contact with extraterrestrial life? (S1, ep 10)
New Mexico: Every inexplicable flash or strange aircraft makes us believe we've spotted extraterrestrials - but what if they've been watching us all along? (S1, ep 7)
Behind The Gates: The Rocky Road Ahead: Matty Blake drills down with the team on their plans to uncover the mysterious objects that are buried in the Mesa on Skinwalker Ranch. (S5, ep 23)
Behind The Gates: Mesa, Mesa, Mesa!: Dr. Travis Taylor digs deeper into the unbelievable discoveries that the team has made in the rocky Mesa on Skinwalker Ranch. (S5, ep 24)
Four US Air Force reservists are pursued by odd lights. Constable Alan Godfrey loses consciousness when he investigates a strange disruption in West Yorkshire. (S2, ep 11)
